        <div class="section-kicker">Workflow</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Audit, migrate, enforce.</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">FlagLint keeps audit, migration, and policy enforcement separate — each step is reviewable and nothing is changed without your explicit review.</p>
        <div class="workflow">
          <div class="workflow-step">
            <span class="step-num">1</span>
            <h3>Audit</h3>
            <p>Get a risk-ranked overview for engineers before touching code. Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">scan</code> when automation needs file-level structured inventory.</p>
            <code class="mini-code">npx flaglint audit ./src</code>
            <code class="mini-code">npx flaglint scan ./src --format json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="workflow-step">
            <span class="step-num">2</span>
            <h3>Migrate</h3>
            <p>Preview diffs, then apply only proven safe call-site rewrites.</p>
            <code class="mini-code">npx flaglint migrate ./src --dry-run</code>
          </div>
          <div class="workflow-step">
            <span class="step-num">3</span>
            <h3>Enforce</h3>
            <p>Block new direct LaunchDarkly evaluation calls in pull requests.</p>
            <code class="mini-code">npx flaglint validate ./src --no-direct-launchdarkly</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

